In young people, I love the work Leo Arill does.
For you, what is your greatest success in the federation?
Having been one of the most glorious times of the national team between 1988 and 1995, and the fact that at the beginning of the 1990s, the BC had up to 17 teams in a season.
What do you have to do?
There are things I would have liked to put in place, such as the regionalization of minor categories.
